<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 21 at 9:15PM EDT  by NWS Grand Rapids</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of Calhoun and
southeastern Kalamazoo Counties through 1000 PM EDT...
At 915 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Battle Creek to 5 miles northeast of Three
Rivers. Movement was east at 45 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Albion...              Marshall...            Battle Creek...
Vicksburg...           Homer...               Union City...
Climax...              Burlington...          Brownlee Park...
Level Park-Oak Park... Fulton...              Marengo...
Athens...              Tekonsha...            Pine Creek...
Ceresco...             Scotts...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
